  <%!-- ══════════════ SECTION 2: THE PROBLEM ══════════════ --%>
  <section id="problem" class="landing-section" aria-labelledby="problem-heading">
    <div class="window landing-window landing-window--reveal">
      <div class="title-bar">
        <div class="title-bar-text">C:\TRUTH\about_modern_chat.txt</div>
        <div class="title-bar-controls">
          <button aria-label="Minimize" disabled></button>
          <button aria-label="Maximize" disabled></button>
          <button aria-label="Close" disabled></button>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="window-body">
        <h2 id="problem-heading" class="landing-section__headline">
          <.icon_warning class="licon licon-16" /> Your community isn&rsquo;t yours.
        </h2>

        <p>
          You built a community on Discord. Or on Slack.
          Months of investment. Thousands of messages. Real connections.
        </p>
        <p>Now think about this:</p>

        <div class="sunken-panel">
          <ul class="landing-problem-list">
            <li>
              <.icon_ban class="licon licon-16" />
              <span>
                <strong>Discord can ban your server tomorrow.</strong>
                No warning. No appeal. No backup.
              </span>
            </li>
            <li>
              <.icon_dollar class="licon licon-16" />
              <span>
                <strong>Slack charges for messages you already sent.</strong>
                Your history, behind a paywall.
              </span>
            </li>
            <li>
              <.icon_globe_blocked class="licon licon-16" />
              <span>
                <strong>Telegram can be blocked in your entire country.</strong>
                One court order and your community is gone.
              </span>
            </li>
            <li>
              <.icon_document_alert class="licon licon-16" />
              <span>
                <strong>Twitter/X changed the DM rules. Again.</strong>
                Your contact network, hostage to a corporation.
              </span>
            </li>
            <li>
              <.icon_robot class="licon licon-16" />
              <span>
                <strong>Your data trains another company&rsquo;s AI.</strong>
                Your conversations, photos, and files become product.
                You never consented.
              </span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="landing-problem__nostalgia">
          <p>
            <strong>In the 2000s, it wasn&rsquo;t like this.</strong>
          </p>
          <p>
            You ran an IRC server in your basement.
            Connected to EFnet, Undernet, DALnet.
            Your community existed on a network nobody controlled.
            Nobody could take it from you.
          </p>
          <p class="landing-problem__transition">
            Then came the &ldquo;convenience&rdquo;. And with it came the control.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="status-bar">
        <p class="status-bar-field">C:\TRUTH\</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <%!-- ══════════════ SECTION 3: THE SOLUTION ══════════════ --%>
  <section id="solution" class="landing-section" aria-labelledby="solution-heading">
    <h2 id="solution-heading" class="u-sr-only">The Solution</h2>

    <div class="landing-solution-grid">
      <div class="window landing-window landing-window--reveal">
        <div class="title-bar">
          <div class="title-bar-text">What is Retro Hex Chat</div>
          <div class="title-bar-controls">
            <button aria-label="Minimize" disabled></button>
            <button aria-label="Maximize" disabled></button>
            <button aria-label="Close" disabled></button>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="window-body">
          <p>
            Retro Hex Chat is <strong>chat software</strong> that anyone
            can install and run on their own server.
          </p>
          <p>
            Your data lives in <strong>your database</strong>.
            Voice and video calls go <strong>directly between users</strong>
            via WebRTC &mdash; not through the server.
          </p>
          <ul class="landing-solution-bullets">
            <li>
              <.icon_server class="licon licon-16" />
              <span>You own the server, the data, the rules</span>
            </li>
            <li>
              <.icon_p2p class="licon licon-16" /> <span>P2P calls never touch a middleman</span>
            </li>
            <li>
              <.icon_shield class="licon licon-16" />
              <span>No corporation can shut you down</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
          <p>That&rsquo;s it. Simple as that.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="status-bar">
          <p class="status-bar-field"><.icon_checkmark class="licon licon-12" />Ready</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="window landing-window landing-window--reveal">
        <div class="title-bar">
          <div class="title-bar-text">What it&rsquo;s NOT</div>
          <div class="title-bar-controls">
            <button aria-label="Minimize" disabled></button>
            <button aria-label="Maximize" disabled></button>
            <button aria-label="Close" disabled></button>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="window-body">
          <p><strong>Retro Hex Chat is NOT a service.</strong></p>
          <p>There&rsquo;s no company behind it controlling anything.</p>
          <p>There&rsquo;s no &ldquo;Pro&rdquo; or &ldquo;Enterprise&rdquo; plan.</p>
          <p>There&rsquo;s no algorithm deciding what you see.</p>
          <p>It can&rsquo;t be bought, acquired, or shut down.</p>
          <p>
            <strong>
              It&rsquo;s free software. It&rsquo;s yours. It&rsquo;s community-owned.
            </strong>
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="status-bar">
          <p class="status-bar-field"><.icon_checkmark class="licon licon-12" />Ready</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="window landing-window landing-window--reveal landing-solution__p2p">
      <div class="title-bar">
        <div class="title-bar-text">Direct connection. No middleman.</div>
        <div class="title-bar-controls">
          <button aria-label="Minimize" disabled></button>
          <button aria-label="Maximize" disabled></button>
          <button aria-label="Close" disabled></button>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="window-body">
        <p><strong>Voice, video, and files go directly between users.</strong></p>

        <div class="sunken-panel landing-p2p-diagram">
          <pre aria-label="Peer-to-peer connection diagram">
  Alice                                    Bob
  ┌──────┐                          ┌──────┐
  │  &#x1F468;   │  ◄════ WebRTC P2P ════►  │  &#x1F469;   │
  └──────┘     voice / video / files  └──────┘

     │                                    │
     └──────── Server (signaling) ────────┘
               only connects them
               never sees the data</pre>
        </div>

        <p>
          The server only introduces users to each other. Once connected,
          all voice, video, and file data flows <strong>directly</strong>
          between them &mdash; encrypted, private, and fast.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="status-bar">
        <p class="status-bar-field"><.icon_checkmark class="licon licon-12" />Got it</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <%!-- ══════════════ SECTION 4: HOW IT WORKS ══════════════ --%>
  <section id="how-it-works" class="landing-section" aria-labelledby="how-it-works-heading">
    <div class="window landing-window landing-window--reveal">
      <div class="title-bar">
        <div class="title-bar-text">How it works</div>
        <div class="title-bar-controls">
          <button aria-label="Minimize" disabled></button>
          <button aria-label="Maximize" disabled></button>
          <button aria-label="Close" disabled></button>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="window-body">
        <h2 id="how-it-works-heading" class="u-sr-only">How It Works</h2>

        <menu role="tablist" class="landing-tabs" aria-label="How it works concepts">
          <button
            role="tab"
            aria-selected="true"
            aria-controls="tab-server"
            id="tab-btn-server"
            class="landing-tab active"
            type="button"
          >
            <.icon_server class="licon licon-14" /> Your Server
          </button>
          <button
            role="tab"
            aria-selected="false"
            aria-controls="tab-p2p"
            id="tab-btn-p2p"
            class="landing-tab"
            type="button"
          >
            <.icon_p2p class="licon licon-14" /> P2P
          </button>
          <button
            role="tab"
            aria-selected="false"
            aria-controls="tab-privacy"
            id="tab-btn-privacy"
            class="landing-tab"
            type="button"
          >
            <.icon_shield class="licon licon-14" /> Privacy
          </button>
          <button
            role="tab"
            aria-selected="false"
            aria-controls="tab-security"
            id="tab-btn-security"
            class="landing-tab"
            type="button"
          >
            <.icon_security class="licon licon-14" /> Security
          </button>
        </menu>

        <div
          id="tab-server"
          role="tabpanel"
          aria-labelledby="tab-btn-server"
          class="landing-tab-panel"
        >
          <h3>One server. Fully yours.</h3>
          <div class="landing-server-cards">
            <div class="sunken-panel landing-server-card">
              <strong><.icon_database class="licon licon-16" /> Your database</strong> <br />
              Messages, users, channels &mdash; all stored on your machine.
            </div>
            <div class="sunken-panel landing-server-card">
              <strong><.icon_rules class="licon licon-16" /> Your rules</strong> <br />
              You decide who joins, what channels exist, and how moderation works.
            </div>
            <div class="sunken-panel landing-server-card">
              <strong><.icon_backup class="licon licon-16" /> Your backups</strong> <br />
              Export, restore, migrate &mdash; your data is always accessible.
            </div>
          </div>
          <p>
            Anyone can run a server. Install it on a $5/month VPS,
            a Raspberry Pi, or your own hardware. You control everything.
          </p>
          <p>
            <strong>Public:</strong> open to anyone who wants to join.<br />
            <strong>Private:</strong> invite-only, for your company or group.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div
          id="tab-p2p"
          role="tabpanel"
          aria-labelledby="tab-btn-p2p"
          class="landing-tab-panel"
          hidden
        >
          <h3>Direct connections via WebRTC.</h3>
          <div class="sunken-panel landing-p2p-diagram">
            <pre aria-label="WebRTC signaling and data flow diagram">
  1. Alice wants to call Bob
         │
         ▼
  2. Server exchanges signaling (SDP/ICE)
         │
         ▼
  3. Direct P2P connection established
         │
         ▼
  4. Voice, video, and files flow directly
     Alice ◄════════════════════► Bob
         (server is out of the loop)</pre>
          </div>
          <p>
            The server only handles <strong>signaling</strong> &mdash;
            helping users find each other. Once connected, all data flows
            directly between browsers via WebRTC.
          </p>
          <p>
            If a direct connection isn&rsquo;t possible (strict firewalls),
            a <strong>TURN relay</strong> is used as fallback &mdash;
            still encrypted end-to-end.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div
          id="tab-privacy"
          role="tabpanel"
          aria-labelledby="tab-btn-privacy"
          class="landing-tab-panel"
          hidden
        >
          <h3>Big Tech vs. Retro Hex Chat.</h3>
          <div class="sunken-panel landing-privacy-comparison">
            <table>
              <thead>
                <tr>
                  <th></th>
                  <th>Big Tech</th>
                  <th>Retro Hex Chat</th>
                </tr>
              </thead>
              <tbody>
                <tr>
                  <td><strong>Messages</strong></td>
                  <td>Stored on their servers, mined for ads</td>
                  <td>Stored on YOUR server, never leaves</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td><strong>Calls</strong></td>
                  <td>Routed through corporate infrastructure</td>
                  <td>Direct P2P &mdash; server never sees them</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td><strong>Your data</strong></td>
                  <td>Trains their AI, sold to advertisers</td>
                  <td>Stays in your database, period</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td><strong>Code</strong></td>
                  <td>Closed source &mdash; trust us</td>
                  <td>Open source &mdash; verify yourself</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td><strong>Control</strong></td>
                  <td>They can ban you anytime</td>
                  <td>You own the server &mdash; nobody can</td>
                </tr>
              </tbody>
            </table>
          </div>
          <p>
            No tracking. No profiling. No algorithms.
            Your conversations are <strong>your business</strong>.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div
          id="tab-security"
          role="tabpanel"
          aria-labelledby="tab-btn-security"
          class="landing-tab-panel"
          hidden
        >
          <h3>Security at every layer.</h3>
          <div class="sunken-panel">
            <pre aria-label="Security layers diagram">
  Browser ◄──── HTTPS/WSS ────► Server
     │                              │
     │   TLS 1.3 encrypted          │  bcrypt password hashing
     │                              │  rate limiting
     │                              │  CSRF protection
     │
  Browser ◄──── DTLS-SRTP ───► Browser
     │
     │   P2P calls encrypted
     │   end-to-end via WebRTC</pre>
          </div>
          <p>
            <strong>Server connection:</strong> HTTPS and WSS with TLS encryption.<br />
            <strong>P2P calls:</strong> DTLS-SRTP encryption built into WebRTC.<br />
            <strong>Passwords:</strong> bcrypt hashing, never stored in plain text.<br />
            <strong>Open source:</strong> anyone can audit the code. No backdoors.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="status-bar">
        <p class="status-bar-field">4 concepts</p>
        <p class="status-bar-field">~2 min read</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <%!-- ══════════════ SECTION 5: FEATURES ══════════════ --%>
  <section id="features" class="landing-section" aria-labelledby="features-heading">
    <div class="window landing-window landing-window--reveal">
      <div class="title-bar">
        <div class="title-bar-text">What you can do</div>
        <div class="title-bar-controls">
          <button aria-label="Minimize" disabled></button>
          <button aria-label="Maximize" disabled></button>
          <button aria-label="Close" disabled></button>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="window-body">
        <h2 id="features-heading" class="u-sr-only">Features</h2>

        <menu role="tablist" class="landing-tabs" aria-label="Features">
          <button
            role="tab"
            aria-selected="true"
            aria-controls="feat-chat"
            id="feat-btn-chat"
            class="landing-tab active"
            type="button"
          >
            <.icon_chat class="licon licon-14" /> Chat
          </button>
          <button
            role="tab"
            aria-selected="false"
            aria-controls="feat-channels"
            id="feat-btn-channels"
            class="landing-tab"
            type="button"
          >
            <.icon_channels class="licon licon-14" /> Channels
          </button>
          <button
            role="tab"
            aria-selected="false"
            aria-controls="feat-p2p"
            id="feat-btn-p2p"
            class="landing-tab"
            type="button"
          >
            <.icon_p2p class="licon licon-14" /> P2P
          </button>
          <button
            role="tab"
            aria-selected="false"
            aria-controls="feat-admin"
            id="feat-btn-admin"
            class="landing-tab"
            type="button"
          >
            <.icon_rules class="licon licon-14" /> Admin
          </button>
          <button
            role="tab"
            aria-selected="false"
            aria-controls="feat-commands"
            id="feat-btn-commands"
            class="landing-tab"
            type="button"
          >
            <.icon_terminal class="licon licon-14" /> Commands
          </button>
        </menu>

        <div
          id="feat-chat"
          role="tabpanel"
          aria-labelledby="feat-btn-chat"
          class="landing-tab-panel"
        >
          <h3>Real-time chat. Zero refresh. Zero loading.</h3>
          <div class="sunken-panel landing-feature-mockup">
            <pre>
  #elixir
  ───────────────────

  ● alice                           10:23
    Good morning! Anyone tried Phoenix 1.8?

  ● bob                             10:24
    Yes! LiveView is amazing

  ● carol                           10:25
    Agreed, performance is way better</pre>
          </div>
          <ul>
            <li>Real-time messages via WebSocket</li>
            <li>Emoji reactions</li>
            <li>Threads (nested replies)</li>
            <li>Markdown and IRC formatting</li>
            <li>Link previews with metadata</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div
          id="feat-channels"
          role="tabpanel"
          aria-labelledby="feat-btn-channels"
          class="landing-tab-panel"
          hidden
        >
          <h3>Channels are chat rooms.</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Create as many channels as you want</li>
            <li><strong>Public:</strong> anyone can join</li>
            <li><strong>Private:</strong> invite-only</li>
            <li><strong>Protected:</strong> password for restricted channels</li>
            <li>Topic, modes, slow mode &mdash; you control it</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div
          id="feat-p2p"
          role="tabpanel"
          aria-labelledby="feat-btn-p2p"
          class="landing-tab-panel"
          hidden
        >
          <h3>Direct connection between people. Peer-to-peer.</h3>
          <div class="sunken-panel landing-feature-mockup">
            <pre>
  ┌─────────────────────────────────┐
  │  &#x1F3A4; Voice Call with Bob         │
  │                                 │
  │  &#x1F534; 00:03:42                    │
  │                                 │
  │  [Mute] [Camera] [Screen] [End] │
  └─────────────────────────────────┘</pre>
          </div>
          <ul>
            <li>Voice calls &mdash; direct P2P via WebRTC</li>
            <li>Video calls with camera toggle</li>
            <li>File transfer &mdash; send files directly, no server upload</li>
            <li>Picture-in-Picture mode for multitasking</li>
            <li>Media controls: mute, camera, screen share</li>
            <li>End-to-end encrypted by default</li>
            <li>TURN relay fallback for strict firewalls</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div
          id="feat-admin"
          role="tabpanel"
          aria-labelledby="feat-btn-admin"
          class="landing-tab-panel"
          hidden
        >
          <h3>Your server, your rules.</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Full administration panel</li>
            <li>User and channel management</li>
            <li>Rate limiting and moderation</li>
            <li>Real-time logs and metrics</li>
            <li>Backup and restore</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div
          id="feat-commands"
          role="tabpanel"
          aria-labelledby="feat-btn-commands"
          class="landing-tab-panel"
          hidden
        >
          <h3>Powerful IRC-style commands.</h3>
          <div class="sunken-panel">
            <pre>
  /join #channel     → join a channel
  /msg @nick text    → direct message
  /nick new_nick     → change nickname
  /help              → see all commands
  /whois @nick       → info about a user</pre>
          </div>
          <p>Over 20 commands with smart autocomplete.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="status-bar">
        <p class="status-bar-field">5 categories</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <%!-- ══════════════ SECTION 6: PRIVACY ══════════════ --%>
  <section id="privacy" class="landing-section" aria-labelledby="privacy-heading">
    <div class="window landing-window landing-window--reveal">
      <div class="title-bar">
        <div class="title-bar-text">Privacy</div>
        <div class="title-bar-controls">
          <button aria-label="Minimize" disabled></button>
          <button aria-label="Maximize" disabled></button>
          <button aria-label="Close" disabled></button>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="window-body">
        <h2 id="privacy-heading">Your data stays with you. Period.</h2>

        <div class="sunken-panel landing-privacy-comparison">
          <table>
            <thead>
              <tr>
                <th></th>
                <th>Discord / Slack / Telegram</th>
                <th>Retro Hex Chat</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr>
                <td><strong>Who owns the server?</strong></td>
                <td>A corporation</td>
                <td>You</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><strong>Where are messages stored?</strong></td>
                <td>Their cloud, their terms</td>
                <td>Your server, your database</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><strong>Voice and video calls</strong></td>
                <td>Routed through their servers</td>
                <td>Direct P2P via WebRTC</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><strong>Can they read your messages?</strong></td>
                <td>Yes &mdash; and they do</td>
                <td>No &mdash; only you have access</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><strong>Data used for AI training?</strong></td>
                <td>Often, and without consent</td>
                <td>Never. Your data is yours.</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><strong>Can they ban your community?</strong></td>
                <td>Yes, at any time</td>
                <td>No &mdash; you own the server</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><strong>Source code</strong></td>
                <td>Closed. Trust them blindly.</td>
                <td>Open source. Audit it yourself.</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>

        <p>
          No tracking. No profiling. No data harvesting.
          Just a chat server that <strong>respects your privacy</strong>.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="status-bar">
        <p class="status-bar-field">Your data. Your rules.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <%!-- ══════════════ SECTION 7: RUN YOUR OWN ══════════════ --%>
  <section id="install" class="landing-section" aria-labelledby="install-heading">
    <div class="window landing-window landing-window--reveal">
      <div class="title-bar">
        <div class="title-bar-text">C:\SETUP\install_server.exe</div>
        <div class="title-bar-controls">
          <button aria-label="Minimize" disabled></button>
          <button aria-label="Maximize" disabled></button>
          <button aria-label="Close" disabled></button>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="window-body">
        <h2 id="install-heading">Want your own server? Three steps.</h2>

        <div class="landing-install-steps">
          <fieldset>
            <legend><.icon_git class="licon licon-14" /> Step 1 &mdash; Clone</legend>
            <pre class="landing-terminal">$ git clone https://github.com/rodrigomarchi/retro_hex_chat.git
$ cd retro_hex_chat</pre>
          </fieldset>

          <fieldset>
            <legend><.icon_wrench class="licon licon-14" /> Step 2 &mdash; Setup</legend>
            <pre class="landing-terminal">$ make setup</pre>
          </fieldset>

          <fieldset>
            <legend><.icon_terminal class="licon licon-14" /> Step 3 &mdash; Run</legend>
            <pre class="landing-terminal">$ make server
[info] Running RetroHexChatWeb.Endpoint at http://localhost:4000</pre>
          </fieldset>
        </div>

        <p>
          <strong>Requirements:</strong>
          Elixir 1.17+, PostgreSQL 16+, Node.js 20+.<br /> A $5/month VPS handles it just fine.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="status-bar">
        <p class="status-bar-field">Installation complete</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

